Problem:
--------
Given an integer array of size n, find all elements that appear more than ⌊ n/3 ⌋ times.

Example 1:
Input: nums = [3,2,3]
Output: [3]

Example 2:
Input: nums = [1]
Output: [1]

Example 3:
Input: nums = [1,2]
Output: [1,2]
 
Constraints:
1 <= nums.length <= 5 * 10^4
-10^9 <= nums[i] <= 10^9
Follow up: Could you solve the problem in linear time and in O(1) space?

Solution:
--------
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> majorityElement(int[] nums) {
        List<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();
        int cnt1=0,cnt2=0;
        int n=nums.length;
        int candidate1=Integer.MIN_VALUE,candidate2=Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for(int num:nums){
            if(num==candidate1){
                cnt1++;
            }
            else if(num==candidate2){
                cnt2++;
            }
            else if(cnt1==0){
                candidate1=num;
                cnt1=1;
            }
            else if(cnt2==0){
                candidate2=num;
                cnt2=1;
            }
            else{
                cnt1--;
                cnt2--;
            }
        }
        cnt1=0;
        cnt2=0;
        for(int num:nums){
            if(num==candidate1){
                cnt1++;
            }
            if(num==candidate2){
                cnt2++;
            }
        }
        if(cnt1>n/3){
           ans.add(candidate1);
        }
         if(cnt2>n/3){
           ans.add(candidate2);
        }
        return ans;
    }
}

Time Complexity: O(N)
Space Complexity: O(1)
